<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-22 01:00 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AP Top News at 1 a.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    Tuesday, Feb. 22, 2000
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Texas Inmates Take Officer Hostage
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   LIVINGSTON, Texas (AP) -- Two death row inmates who were part of a botched
escape in 1998 took a female guard hostage Monday in a new prison that was
supposed to be more secure. The guard was taking one inmate back to his cell at
about 4:15 p.m. when he and another inmate overpowered her, said Texas
Department of Criminal Justice spokesman Larry Fitzgerald. One inmate had
somehow jimmied his cell door, Fitzgerald said. "They have no place to go.
Officers have sealed off the area," he said. "She has not been threatened or
harmed in any way, but it is a tense situation."
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Gore, Bradley Spar in Harlem Debate
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) -- In an angry Harlem debate, Al Gore accused Bill Bradley of
attack tactics that "divide us as Democrats," while the challenger described the
vice president as a sometime conservative with a suspect record on affirmative
action. The tone of the argument on the stage of the historic Apollo Theater was
set at the start, when the presidential rivals agreed that they'd both take
steps against racial profiling -- and immediately tried to turn the question
against each other. The 90-minute debate -- the candidates ninth presidential
debate -- was televised by CNN. The largely black audience cheered, applauded,
jeered, sometimes booed. Neither candidate was spared the raucous reactions.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
China Warns of Taiwan Attack
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   BEIJING (AP) -- China warned Monday that it might attack Taiwan if the
island's leaders indefinitely refuse to talk unification. The threat, which came
a month before Taiwan's presidential election campaign, was intended to increase
the pressure on Taiwan's three presidential candidates. Although there was no
immediate reaction from Taiwan's government or the candidates' camps, policy
toward China has been at the center of the campaign. Already this month, China
sailed its newly acquired, destroyer through the Taiwan Strait.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Space Shuttle To Land in California
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) -- NASA has informed space shuttle Endeavour's
astronauts that the backup landing site at Edwards Air Force Base in California
appears to be the "only viable option" for tomorrow's landing. Clouds and high
wind were forecast at Cape Canaveral in Florida. The last time NASA had to
divert a space shuttle to Edwards was in 1996. With their mapping of Earth
completed, the astronauts pulled in a 197-foot radar antenna mast after
struggling with it for two tense hours.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
TV Groom Denies Abuse Allegations
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   ENCINITAS, Calif. (AP) -- The husband from "Who Wants to Marry a
Multimillionaire?" returned to his house alone after his Caribbean honeymoon and
angrily denied that he had abused an ex-girlfriend. Fox TV canceled a
rebroadcast of the show after learning that a restraining order was issued in
1991 against Rick Rockwell because an ex-girlfriend accused him of hitting and
threatening to kill her. "At no time have I ever struck any of my girlfriends,
ever, for any reason," Rockwell, 42, told KGTV on Sunday night outside his home
in Encinitas, a coastal city 25 miles north of San Diego.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Tokyo Stocks Down at Midday
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   TOKYO (AP) -- The Nikkei, which rose some 140 points early the session,
finished the morning down 50.79 to 19,492.96 on Tuesday. On Monday, the average
closed down 245.28 points. Investors also remained cautious over uncertainty
about the direction of New York markets. On Friday, the Dow Jones industrial
average tumbled 295.05 points, or 2.8 percent, to close at 10,219.52. U.S.
financial markets were closed Monday in observance of Presidents Day.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Jazz 96, Hawks 94
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Armen Gilliam converted a layup off an assist from
John Stockton with 2.2 seconds left Monday night to give the Utah Jazz a 96-94
come-from-behind victory over the Atlanta Hawks. Karl Malone led all scorers
with 25 points, including eight in the fourth quarter. Jeff Hornacek added 17.
Isaiah Rider led the Hawks with 22 points. Jim Jackson added 15 points and
Dikembe Mutombo put in 12 points and grabbed 16 rebounds.
</P>
