<HEADLINE> Stock Prices Open Higher  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices opened higher on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Industrial Average is up 10 points in early trading. Advancing
issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold a slim lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 23 points and the Standard and Poor's
500 Stock Index is up 2 points.
</P>
<P>
	   Wall Street gets back to work after a three-day weekend for Presidents Day.
</P>
<P>
	   And traders no doubt needed the extra day of rest after Friday's
whitewashing.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq and the S&AMP;P 500 each fell more than three percent to close out
last week, with the Dow down nearly that much.
</P>
<P>
	   There will be little in the way of market-moving news this week. The
economic calendar is particularly light, as is the list of companies reporting
earnings.
</P>
<P>
	   Fed chairman Alan Greenspan is due back on Capitol Hill Wednesday, but his
testimony is largely expected to be a replay of his remarks from last week.
</P>
</TEXT>
