the nation's third largest oil refiner in a bid to cut costs.
General Sekiyu KK, an oil distributor that operates a national
chain of gas stations, and Tonen Corp., an oil refiner, said they
will combine their businesses effective July 1. The new company
will be called Tonen General Sekiyu KK. General Sekiyu and Tonen
plan to reduce their combined work force of 2,700 employees by 300
people, or 11.1 percent, mostly through voluntary retirement.
</P>
<P>
