deal is expected to close in the second quarter. Liberty officials
said today they will continue to look for a new owner for the
Nuggets, the Avalanche, and the new Pepsi Center stadium in Denver.
Liberty planned to buy the non-sports assets of the Denver-based
Ascent last year but the deal fell through. The company also
provides pay-per-view programming for hotels and satellite service
and maintenance to NBC.
</P>
