<HEADLINE> Sextuplets Born in Saudi Arabia  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   RIYADH, Saudi Arabia (AP) -- A Saudi woman was in stable condition after
giving birth to sextuplets, a hospital official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
	   The babies weighed between 4 and 5.5 pounds, ``and they are all fine,'' an
official at King Khaled University hospital said on condition of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
	   The mother, who was not identified, had a Caesarean delivery on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
	   A children's food company has pledged to provide baby formula for the
children for the next two years, and another company said it would provide
diapers for a two-year period.
</P>
<P>
	   In 1998, another Saudi woman gave birth to septuplets, one of two sets of
surviving septuplets in the world. The other septuplets were born the same year
to an American family in Iowa.
</P>
