<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   Tuesday, Feb. 22, 2000
</P>
<P>
	   Dow Ends Up 85.32; Nasdaq Off 31.07
</P>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) -- Prices were mixed in a volatile day on Wall
Street today as investors, while searching for bargain stocks, were
dogged by worries about interest rates. The Dow Jones industrial
average, which had been down as much as 115 points early in the
day, rallied to close up 85.32 at 10,304.84. The technology-focused
Nasdaq composite index, however, was unable to shake off concerns
about interest rates and fell 31.07 to 4,380.67. ``The average
investor is looking for the opportunity to step in here, but with
the pressure that's been created by the Federal Reserve, this could
drag on for a while,'' Bob Dickey, managing director of technical
analysis at Dain Rauscher Wessels, said.
</P>
