	   ARLINGTON, Va. (AP) -- The union representing US Airways flight
attendants has rejecting binding arbitration in a move that could
set the stage for a threatened series of strikes. The Association
of Flight Attendants told the National Mediation Board of its
decision today. It is now up to the board to start the clock on a
30 day cooling-off period. If no deal is reached when that period
expires, the union can strike.
</P>
