about 10 percent of its global work force over the next five years.
It also will close 100 of its 250 production sites as it regroups
manufacturing operations into regional networks. Most of the job
cuts will come in Europe and the Americas. The company also
announced that profits fell 5 percent last year. Unilever is the
company behind the brands Dove soap, Lipton tea, Breyer's ice cream
and Close-Up toothpaste. Unilever stock was up 1 at 25 3/4.
