March by a group of creditors, claiming total debts of $1.29
billion. The company has so far closed 122 stores and cut 5,000
jobs. It currently has about 16,000 full-time employees at its
Nashville offices, three distribution centers and 221 stores in 32
states. It is reducing the number of products it sells and
expanding its core jewelry business, especially diamonds, and its
Internet sales.
</P>
