<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Limited Earnings Up 37 Percent  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- The Limited Inc. said its fourth-quarter earnings
rose 37 percent, beating analyst expectations, as the retailer reported improved
sales at its clothing stores.
</P>
<P>
	   Limited said adjusted net income for the three months ended Jan. 29 came to
$294.9 million, or $1.31 per share, compared with $215.8 million, or 92 cents
per share, for the same quarter a year ago.
</P>
<P>
	   Analysts surveyed by First Call expected earnings of $1.18 per share.
</P>
<P>
	   Sales totaled $3.3 billion, compared with $3.1 billion.
</P>
<P>
	   The figures reflect the August spinoff of Too Inc. and the May 1998
split-off of Abercrombie &AMP; Fitch Co. as if they had occurred at the beginning of
1998, the company said. They also exclude one-time items.
</P>
<P>
	   Without the adjustment, fourth-quarter earnings increased 39 percent, to
$316.5 million, or $1.41 per share, compared to earnings of $228.2 million, or
97 cents per share.
</P>
<P>
	   Limited, which has been restructuring its clothing chains including Limited,
Express, Lane Bryant and Lerner New York, benefited from closing 301 stores in
1999. Over the past five years, the company has shut more than 1,050 stores, and
another 108 are scheduled to close this year.
</P>
<P>
	   The company began the restructuring after losing customers in the early and
mid-1990s to other merchants who offered more casual, classic clothes and lower
prices.
</P>
<P>
	   Limited also operates Structure stores and owns 84 percent of Intimate
Brands Inc., which includes Victoria's Secret,Bath &AMP; Body Works and White Barn
Candle Co. stores.
</P>
<P>
	   For the year, Limited's adjusted net income increased 40 percent, to $445.5
million, or $1.93 per share, from $318 million, or $1.35 per share. Sales were
$9.5 billion, compared with $8.8 billion.
</P>
<P>
	   Without the adjustment, earnings for the year were $460.8 million, or $2 per
share, compared with $2 billion, or $8.29 per share.
</P>
<P>
	   Shares in The Limited closed at $31.44 Tuesday on the New York Stock
Exchange, up 81 cents or about 2.6 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
