his face, neck, chest and right arm Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
	   Alerted by neighbors, police said they arrived to find Whitcomb lying face
down in the street while the dogs tore away at his body. Two officers fired
their guns and killed one dog. The other was captured and was being kept at the
city's animal control center.
</P>
<P>
