<P>
	   Hours after Rochester Mayor William Johnson called on changes in state law
as a result of the mauling, another pit bull attack was reported in the city.
</P>
<P>
	   Late Tuesday afternoon, a pit bull jumped a fence and attacked several
people including one who was treated at a hospital, police said. Two other
people were injured, but refused to be treated by ambulance personel.
</P>
<P>
	   City police cornered the pit bull and shot it.
