<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brown &AMP; Williamson Plans Shutdown  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    MACON, Ga. (AP) -- Brown &AMP; Williamson said Tuesday it will close its Macon
cigarette manufacturing plant for a week next month because of slow sales.
</P>
<P>
	   The March 11-18 hiatus will idle 2,000 workers and help the company adjust
inventories at the factory, which has an annual production capacity of 150
billion cigarettes.
</P>
<P>
	   Jeff Myhand, vice president of manufacturing and operations, blamed higher
cigarette taxes and prices for the sales decline.
</P>
<P>
	   The Macon plant has had periodic "down days" over the last year to help
adjust inventory. Brown &AMP; Williamson produces brands such as KOOL, Lucky Strike,
Carlton, Capri and Misty at the facility.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
