<HEADLINE> Canadiens 1, Coyotes 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    MONTREAL (AP) -- Jeff Hackett made 27 saves for his first shutout of the
season, and Benoit Brunet scored with less than seven minutes left in the
Montreal Canadiens' 1-0 victory over the Phoenix Coyotes on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
	   The win was Montreal's sixth in a row, its longest winning streak since
seven straight in November 1997. The Canadiens are 12-2-2-2 since Jan. 11.
</P>
<P>
	   Hackett, who has won his last five games, got his first shutout since last
March 24 at Edmonton. Hackett, 6-1-1 in his last eight starts, and teammate Jose
Theodore have combined for six shutouts this season. Theodore is tied with the
Buffalo's Martin Biron for the individual lead with five.
</P>
<P>
	   Brunet redirected Patrice Brisebois' slap shot from the point past Sean
Burke at 12:34 of the third, just seconds after Phoenix defenseman Radoslav
Suchy left the penalty box.
</P>
<P>
	   Canadiens captain Saku Koivu, who returned after missing the previous 40
games with a dislocated left shoulder, assisted on Brunet's goal with a pass to
Brisebois at the point.
</P>
<P>
	   Martin Rucinsky, Montreal's leading scorer with 38 points, needed five
stitches to close a cut to the inside of his lower lip when he was struck in the
mouth by Phoenix defenseman Stan Neckar's stick in the first period.
</P>
</TEXT>
